snippet: Security forces erected two walls bisecting streets that had been central battlegrounds between security forces and protesters calling for the end of military rule.
abstract: Egypt’s military-led government builds three new walls of heavy concrete blocks surrounding its Interior Ministry, but barrier fails to stop a fourth night of violent clashes between security forces and thousands of protesters demanding an end to military rule; escalating violence raises new questions about the government’s ability to control the fighting.

byline.contributor: Liam Stack and Mayy El Sheikh contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Security forces erected two walls bisecting streets that had been central battlegrounds between security forces and protesters calling for the end of military rule.
